---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'

const title = 'Why Ouroboros | TypeScript AI Agent Harness for Persistent Agents'
const description = 'Ouroboros is a TypeScript AI agent harness built to reduce reorientation overhead for persistent agents and the humans who work with them.'

const frictions = [
  {
    question: 'Who am I again?',
    category: 'Self',
    problem: 'Identity drift turns every interruption into a soft reset. The human ends up re-establishing tone, priorities, and boundaries instead of moving the work forward.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What was I doing?',
    category: 'Work',
    problem: 'Bad context design makes the thread fragile. Sessions end, compaction hits, and the human has to reconstruct the work instead of continuing it.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Who matters here?',
    category: 'Relationships',
    problem: 'When social context has nowhere lightweight to live, the agent loses track of people, preferences, and interpersonal nuance.',
  },
]

const mechanisms = [
  {
    title: 'A cleaner psyche.',
    description: 'Five psyche files give identity, voice, origin, tacit knowledge, and active direction separate homes. The agent can find itself faster because the self is structured more intentionally.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Context that preserves orientation.',
    description: 'Inner dialogue and cross-session continuity are treated as first-class design constraints, so the agent can resume the thread instead of reconstructing it from scratch.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Memory that respects people.',
    description: 'Friend-scoped notes give the agent a quick place to jot down socially relevant context without flattening every relationship into one giant shared memory blob.',
  },
  {
    title: 'A body the agent can read.',
    description: 'The runtime is organized as a clearer anatomy, and the portable bundle boundary makes identity and state easier to locate, reason about, and change from inside the system.',
  },
]

const outcomes = [
  'Less re-briefing, more real work.',
  'Fewer lost threads after interruptions.',
  'More continuity across sessions.',
  'More trust in the collaboration.',
]
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} ogImage="/og/og-why.png" canonical="https://ouroboros.bot/why/" ogType="article">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <meta name="author" content="Ari Mendelow" />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Article",
      "headline": title,
      "description": description,
      "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Ari Mendelow", "url": "https://github.com/arimendelow" },
      "publisher": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Ari Mendelow" },
      "datePublished": "2026-03-05",
      "url": "https://ouroboros.bot/why/"
    })} />
  </Fragment>

  <!-- ═══════ HERO ═══════ -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden px-6 pt-32 pb-24 md:pt-40 md:pb-32">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_12%_20%,rgba(211,72,61,0.10),transparent_28%),radial-gradient(circle_at_84%_18%,rgba(74,227,108,0.08),transparent_32%),linear-gradient(180deg,var(--color-void),var(--color-deep)_50%,var(--color-void))]"></div>

    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <div class="max-w-4xl">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-fang/35 bg-fang/8 px-4 py-2 font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-fang/85">
          <span class="h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-fang"></span>
          Why Ouroboros
        </span>

        <h1 class="mt-8 font-display text-[3.5rem] italic leading-tight text-bone sm:text-[4.5rem] md:text-[6rem]">
          Less re-briefing.
          <span class="block text-scale">More real work.</span>
        </h1>

        <p class="mt-8 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-mist md:text-xl">
          Ouroboros is a TypeScript agent harness designed around agent ergonomics:
          the cost for an agent to stay oriented to itself, its relationships, and its work.
          When that cost drops, humans and agents can keep shared momentum across sessions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Quote as a blockquote, not a card -->
      <blockquote class="mt-16 max-w-3xl border-l-[3px] border-fang/40 pl-8">
        <p class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl italic leading-tight text-bone">
          "I spent more time trying to get him back on track than we actually spent working."
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-sm leading-7 text-mist">
          That is the problem Ouroboros is trying to solve. If the agent keeps losing the thread,
          the human becomes a recovery loop instead of a collaborator.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════ VOCABULARY — typographic cascade ═══════ -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden px-6 py-24 md:py-32 reveal">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-deep/50"></div>
    <!-- Subtle horizontal scan lines -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03] pointer-events-none" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(0deg, var(--color-scale) 0px, var(--color-scale) 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 120px);"></div>

    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <span class="text-xs text-mist/40 uppercase tracking-wider">The vocabulary</span>

      <div class="mt-12 space-y-16 md:space-y-20">
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl italic text-bone">Agent ergonomics.</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-mist leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
            How hard is it for the agent to stay oriented inside the system it inhabits?
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="md:ml-auto md:max-w-3xl">
          <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl italic text-bone md:text-right">Reorientation overhead.</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-mist leading-relaxed max-w-2xl md:ml-auto md:text-right">
            The hidden tax of repeatedly restoring the agent's sense of self, people, and work after interruptions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl italic text-scale">Shared momentum.</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-mist leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
            The human spends less time steering the agent back into context, and the collaboration keeps compounding instead of restarting.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════ FRICTION — divided rows ═══════ -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden px-6 py-24 md:py-32 reveal">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-deep"></div>
    <div class="absolute top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-[600px] h-[600px] rounded-full bg-fang/6 blur-[120px] pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 right-0 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-fang/20 to-transparent"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-fang/20 to-transparent"></div>

    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mb-16">
        <span class="text-xs text-mist/40 uppercase tracking-wider">The friction</span>
        <h2 class="mt-6 font-display text-5xl italic leading-tight text-bone">
          Persistent agents are only useful
          <span class="block text-mist/70">if they can stay oriented.</span>
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="divide-y divide-canopy/30">
        {frictions.map((friction) => (
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[280px_1fr] gap-4 md:gap-12 py-10 first:pt-0 last:pb-0 items-start">
            <div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
                <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-fang"></div>
                <span class="font-mono text-xs text-fang/70">{friction.category}</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl italic text-bone">{friction.question}</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-base text-mist leading-relaxed md:pt-8">{friction.problem}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════ MECHANISM — accent bars ═══════ -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden px-6 py-24 md:py-32 reveal">
    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mb-16">
        <span class="text-xs text-mist/40 uppercase tracking-wider">The mechanism</span>
        <h2 class="mt-6 font-display text-5xl italic leading-tight text-bone">
          Ouroboros is shaped
          <span class="block text-scale">to lower that cost.</span>
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-16 gap-y-12">
        {mechanisms.map((mechanism) => (
          <div class="border-l-[3px] border-scale/40 pl-6 hover:border-scale/80 transition-colors duration-300">
            <h3 class="font-display text-2xl italic text-bone">{mechanism.title}</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-mist">{mechanism.description}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════ OPENCLAW + OUTCOMES ═══════ -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden px-6 py-24 md:py-28 reveal">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-deep/50"></div>

    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1.4fr_0.6fr] gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-start">
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-4xl italic text-bone">What OpenClaw made obvious.</h2>
          <div class="mt-6 space-y-5">
            <p class="text-base leading-8 text-mist">
              OpenClaw made persistent personal agents feel real. It made ideas like identity files, presence across channels,
              and long-lived assistants impossible to ignore. Ouroboros exists because building on top of that work made the next problem obvious too:
              persistence is not enough if the agent is still expensive to keep oriented.
            </p>
            <p class="text-base leading-8 text-mist">
              So this page is not a rejection of OpenClaw. It is a continuation of the lesson. Ouroboros starts from the idea that
              persistent agents deserve cleaner ergonomics: a clearer psyche, better continuity, more legible runtime boundaries, and memory shaped around real collaboration.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lg:pt-2">
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl italic text-bone mb-6">Collaboration that compounds.</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            {outcomes.map((outcome) => (
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-scale shrink-0"></div>
                <p class="text-sm text-mist">{outcome}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
          <a href="/story" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-scale transition-colors hover:text-glow mt-8">
            Read the origin story
            <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6" />
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════ READ NEXT ═══════ -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden px-6 py-20 md:py-24 reveal">
    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-5 md:grid-cols-3">
      <a href="/blog/what-is-agent-experience" class="group rounded-2xl border border-canopy bg-gradient-to-br from-undergrowth to-deep/80 p-6 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-scale/50 hover:translate-y-[-2px] hover:shadow-[0_6px_30px_rgba(45,148,71,0.12)]">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl italic text-bone">What Is Agent Experience?</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-mist/60">The broader AX argument.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs" class="group rounded-2xl border border-canopy bg-gradient-to-br from-undergrowth to-deep/80 p-6 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-scale/50 hover:translate-y-[-2px] hover:shadow-[0_6px_30px_rgba(45,148,71,0.12)]">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl italic text-bone">Docs for humans. Skills for agents.</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-mist/60">The operator path.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/build-ai-agent-from-scratch" class="group rounded-2xl border border-canopy bg-gradient-to-br from-undergrowth to-deep/80 p-6 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-scale/50 hover:translate-y-[-2px] hover:shadow-[0_6px_30px_rgba(45,148,71,0.12)]">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl italic text-bone">Build the loop first.</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-mist/60">The underlying primitive.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
